  "text": "## How Kubernetes Creates a Deployment: End-to-End Trace\n\n### Layer 1: Client Library (kubernetes-client-go)\n\nWhen a user creates a Deployment, they call:\n```go\ndeploymentsClient.Create(ctx, deployment, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n```\n\nThe `deploymentsClient` is of type `deployments` (kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go:66), which implements the `DeploymentInterface` interface. This struct embeds `*gentype.ClientWithListAndApply` which provides the actual Create method implementation.\n\nThe Create method constructs an HTTP POST request using the kubernetes-client-go REST client. In `rest/client.go:215`, the `RESTClient.Post()` method returns a new REST request that will POST to the endpoint `/apis/apps/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/deployments`. The request body contains the serialized Deployment object and is sent via `request.Do(ctx)` which executes the HTTP request against the API server.\n\n### Layer 2: API Server Handler (kubernetes)\n\nThe Kubernetes API server receives the POST request and routes it to the REST handler. In `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go:53-237`, the `createHandler` function processes the request:\n\n1. Line 102-113: Parses CreateOptions from query parameters\n2. Line 117-127: Decodes the request body into a Deployment object\n3. Line 182-191: Calls the REST storage's Create method: `r.Create(ctx, name, obj, validationFunc, options)`\n\nThis delegates to the storage layer via the `REST` struct defined in `pkg/registry/apps/deployment/storage/storage.go:87-90`. The REST struct embeds `*genericregistry.Store` which implements the actual Create operation.\n\n### Layer 3: Storage Handler (kubernetes)\n\nThe `REST.Create()` method (inherited from `genericregistry.Store`) in `pkg/registry/apps/deployment/storage/storage.go:92-116` sets up the storage configuration:\n\n1. Creates a new store with deployment-specific strategy and options\n2. Configures validation strategy via `deployment.Strategy` \n3. Calls `store.CompleteWithOptions()` which connects to the etcd backend\n\nThe store then encodes the Deployment object and prepares it for persistence. The key is formed as `/kubernetes.io/deployments/namespaces/{namespace}/name/{name}` and the value is the encoded Deployment protobuf.\n\n### Layer 4: etcd Storage Backend (etcd-io/etcd)\n\nThe kubernetes API server uses etcd as its distributed key-value store backend. The store sends a Put request to etcd via the gRPC v3 API.\n\nIn `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/key.go:27-39`, the `kvServer` struct receives the Put request at the RPC layer:\n- `NewKVServer(s *etcdserver.EtcdServer)` creates the server (line 37-39)\n- `kvServer.Put(ctx context.Context, r *pb.PutRequest)` handles incoming Put requests (lines 55-67)\n\nThe kvServer delegates to the underlying etcd server:\n```go\nresp, err := s.kv.Put(ctx, r)  // line 60\n```\n\nThis calls `EtcdServer.Put()` in `server/etcdserver/v3_server.go:139-146`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *EtcdServer) Put(ctx context.Context, r *pb.PutRequest) (*pb.PutResponse, error) {\n    ctx = context.WithValue(ctx, traceutil.StartTimeKey, time.Now())\n    resp, err := s.raftRequest(ctx, pb.InternalRaftRequest{Put: r})\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    return resp.(*pb.PutResponse), nil\n}\n```\n\nThe Put request is wrapped in an InternalRaftRequest and sent to the Raft consensus engine via `s.raftRequest()` (line 141).\n\nThe request is:\n1. Proposed to the Raft cluster for consensus (raftRequest → processInternalRaftRequestOnce → s.r.Propose)\n2. Replicated across the cluster members\n3. Applied to the MVCC key-value store once committed\n4. Persisted to the bbolt embedded BoltDB backend\n\nThe `RaftKV` interface (lines 54-60) defines the contract that the EtcdServer implements for Put operations, ensuring the Deployment is durably stored in the distributed etcd cluster.\n\n### Summary of the Call Chain\n\n1. **Client**: `deploymentsClient.Create()` → `rest.Post().Body().Do(ctx)` → HTTP POST to API server\n2. **API Server**: `handlers.CreateResource()` → `handlers.createHandler()` → `REST.Create()`\n3. **Storage**: `genericregistry.Store.Create()` → encodes object and calls etcd backend\n4. **etcd**: `kvServer.Put()` → `EtcdServer.Put()` → `raftRequest()` → applies to MVCC store → persists to bbolt backend\n\nThis design ensures the Deployment object is:\n- Validated and admitted at the API server level\n- Stored durably in etcd with consensus guarantees\n- Accessible to controllers and watchers immediately after creation\n- Recoverable in case of failures due to Raft replication"
